@node "Disclaimer" "Disclaimer"

 - Disclaimer - 

The  author  of  XAmyBW can not be held responsible for any damage that this
program  or  the  manual  that  came with it might cause.  If you are using
XAmyBW,  you  will  do  so  at YOUR OWN RISK.  Note however that it has been
thoroughly  tested using "Enforcer" as well as "Mungwall".  But this is, of
course,  no  guarantee  that it is 100% bug-free, and can/will not crash at
some rare occasion.


@endnode

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 - Introduction - 

XAmyBW  is  a  program  that  will  enable  you to read and write electronic
messages,  using  the Xenolink BBS System.

It is still in early beta stage but it works..

Have fun!


@endnode

@node "System_Requirements" "System Requirements"

 - System Requirements - 

To use XAmyBW you need at least Kickstart 2.04 and xxMb of memory, a harddisk is
not necessary but definitely recommended.  You also need these libraries to
run XAmyBW:

   - reqtools.library  version 38+
   - diskfont.library  version 37+
   - EAGUI.library     version 1.1+
   
and ofcourse Xenolink

A text editor (e.g.  Ed or CEd) to edit replies

XAmyBW has been tested on the following systems:

A500 KS3.01 / 20Mb
A4000/40 KS3.0 /20MB
A2000/30 KS3.0 / 22MB

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

 - Installation -

Please NOTICE this beta version has no install script yet.

Just make a directory XAmyBW en copy the program en the guide
to this directory, after that check to see if you have the EAGUI.library
en if not copy that one to your libs directory...

To install XAmyBW all you have to do is double click on the "Install"  icon.
The  installation script will ask you for a destination directory where you
want XAmyBW to be installed. If you enter a directory that doesn't exist, it
will be created (if possible). If you are upgrading from a previous version
enter the directory of the old version ("XAmyBW:"). Your own files will  not
be overwritten, just the new executables and the documentation.

The XAmyBW archive should contain the following files:

  - XAmyBW                 (the executable)
  - XAmyBW.names           (sample lookup file)
  - XAmyBW.guide           (this documentation)
  - Install               (installation script)
  - Sample.IFF            (personal message sample)
  - Taglines.txt          (sample tagline file)
  - Libs/EAGUI.library    (gadget creation library)

@endnode

@node "Starting_XAmyBW" "Starting XAmyBW"

 - Starting XAmyBW - 

XAmyBW can be started from the Workbench by double clicking on its icon, or
from  the  CLI.   If  started from the CLI it will not detach from the CLI
window.  To do this you should type "Run >NIL:  < NIL:  XAmyBW".

If XAmyBW was already running a requester will open to inform you. It is not
possible to run two copies of XAmyBW at the same time!

XAmyBW  will reference to its files through the assignment "XAmyBW:" You can
assign  this in your "S:User-Startup" file or, if XAmyBW is started without
this  assignment, "XAmyBW:" will be assigned automatically to the directory
that  holds  the  XAmyBW  executable.  Note that the install script has the
option to add the Assign command to your User-Startup file.

If you  start XAmyBW for the very first time, everything is set to the internal
defaults.

The following TOOLTYPES can be used:

 SETTINGS=<configuration file>           - specifies config file to be used
 ICONIFY                                 - iconify at startup
 CLOSEWB                                 - close Workbench at startup
 ICONFILE=<icon filename>                - icon to use when iconified
 ICONXPOS=<icon x position>              - icon position when iconified
 ICONYPOS=<icon y position>
 ICONNAME=<icon name>                    - name of icon when iconified


These command line options:

 SETTINGS=<configuraton file>
 ICONIFY

@endnode

